{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Fairy}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Fairy|prevnum=763|prev=Tsareena|nextnum=765|next=Oranguru|roundleft=tl|roundright=tr}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Comfey}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Comfey\n|jname=キュワワー\n|jtranslit=Kyuwawā\n|tmname=Cuwawa\n|ndex=764\n|type1=Fairy\n|category=Posy Picker\n|height-ftin=0\'04"\n|height-m=0.1\n|weight-lbs=0.7\n|weight-kg=0.3\n|adex=174\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Flower Veil\n|ability2=Triage\n|abilityd=Natural Cure\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Grass\n|eggcycles=20\n|evtotal=2\n|evsd=2\n|expyield=170\n|lv100exp=800,000\n|gendercode=191\n|color=Green\n|catchrate=60\n|body=01\n|pokefordex=comfey\n|generation=7\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Comfey\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'キュワワー\'\'\' \'\'Cuwawa\'\') is a {{type|Fairy}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation VII]].\n\nIt is not known to [[Evolution|evolve]] into or from any other Pokémon.\n\n==Biology==\nComfey is a small, light green Pokémon with several flowers surrounding it. Its main body has an orange face with oval, light green eyes. On top of its head is a long, fluffy green crest that curls slightly over its face and extends backwards. A thin blue thread is attached to the back of its head, and has several flowers attached to it. The flowers are white, purple, red, and yellow. Comfey usually holds the last flower in its two short arms. On either side of the main crest is a smaller, pale yellow tuft. Comfey is one of the [[List of Pokémon by height|smallest]] Pokémon, tying with {{p|Joltik}}, {{p|Flabébé}}, {{p|Cutiefly}} and {{p|Cosmoem}}.\n\nThis Pokémon stretches sticky vines from its head to pick flowers to create the ring around itself, and will give these rings to those it likes.The flowers can also be thrown at enemy Pokémon to create an opening to either flee or attack. However, it feels uneasy without flowers. Comfey spreads oil from its body along its flower ring. The oil changes the flowers so they emit a soothing fragrance that affects both Comfey and its allies. This aroma can also help with the treatment of people and Pokémon at hospitals.<ref>[http://www.pokemon-sunmoon.com/en-us/pokemon/comfey/ Pokémon Sun and Moon site | Comfey]</ref>\n\nComfey is the [[signature move|only known Pokémon]] capable of learning the move {{m|Floral Healing}}.\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Nurse Joy Comfey.png|thumb|left|250px|Comfey in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===Major appearances===\n====[[Nurse Joy\'s Comfey]]====\nThe [[Nurse Joy]]s in the [[Alola]] [[region]] are assisted by Comfey and {{TP|Nurse Joy|Blissey}}. Nurse Joy\'s Comfey debuted in \'\'[[SM004|First Catch in Alola, Ketchum-Style!]]\'\', which also marked the species\' debut.\n\n====[[Brock\'s Comfey]]====\nBrock was revealed to own a Comfey in \'\'[[SM103|Heart of Fire! Heart of Stone!]]\'\'. He received it from the Nurse Joy from [[Melemele Island]] as thanks for helping her in \'\'[[SM102|Alola, Alola!]]\'\'.\n\n===Minor appearances===\nMultiple {{pkmn2|wild}} Comfey appeared in \'\'[[SM020|Partner Promises!]]\'\'. One placed a {{wp|Lei (garland)|lei}} on {{Ash}} at [[Treasure Island]]. Two of them reappeared in \'\'[[SM102|Alola, Alola!]]\'\', when Ash revisited the island alongside {{ashcl}} and {{an|Misty}}.\n\nThree Comfey appeared in \'\'[[SM046|Deceiving Appearances!]]\'\', with one being seen at [[Aether Paradise]] and the other two appearing in a fantasy. The Comfey at Aether Paradise appeared again in a video in \'\'[[SM049|Mission: Total Recall!]]\'\'.\n\nTwo Comfey appeared in \'\'[[SM072|Sours for the Sweet!]]\'\', during a fantasy.\n\nA {{pkmn|Trainer}}\'s Comfey appeared in \'\'[[SM081|A Young Royal Flame Ignites!]]\'\'.\n\nMultiple Comfey appeared in \'\'[[SM083|Dummy, You Shrunk the Kids!]]\'\', where a shrunken Ash and {{an|Lillie}} rode one by hanging onto its flower ring.\n\nA Comfey appeared in \'\'[[SM084|The Shape of Love to Come!]]\'\', where [[Rapp]] followed it to [[Mina]]\'s location, having found it to be cute.\n\nA Comfey appeared \'\'[[SM112|Got Meltan?]]\'\', where {{AP|Rowlet}} tried to use it in an attempt to replace a {{AP|Meltan}}\'s lost nut head.\n\nA Comfey appeared in \'\'[[SM113|This Magik Moment!]]\'\', where it was seen giving leis out to contestants who answer a question correctly during a quiz show.\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Alola}}\n{{Animedexbody|SM004|Comfey|Rotom Pokédex|Comfey, the Posy Picker Pokémon. A {{t|Fairy}} type. It releases a relaxing scent from the flowers it picks. The scent has a healing effect and can cure [[status condition]]s.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Sun & Moon\'\'|Alola}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Comfey Adventures.png|thumb|170px|Comfey in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\nComfey debuted in \'\'[[PASM02|The Delivery of Rotom and the Girl]]\'\', where it was placed around {{adv|Moon}}\'s neck by a {{tc|Dancer}}. She was immediately startled by it as {{adv|Sun}} laughed from her reaction and commented that he also thought it was a lei when he first came to [[Alola]].\n\nThree Ally Comfey appeared in \'\'[[PASM14|Flash and Cosmog\'s Secret]]\'\', where they helped a {{pkmn2|Totem}} {{p|Lurantis}} fight {{adv|Moon}}.\n\nA Comfey appeared in \'\'[[PASM16|A Photoshoot and the Abandoned Thrifty Megamart]]\'\', where it was seen inside [[Aether Paradise]].\n{{-}}\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Comfey (TCG)}}\n\n==Other appearances==\n===\'\'{{mov|Detective Pikachu}}\'\'===\nA Comfey appeared in \'\'{{mov|Detective Pikachu}}\'\'.\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=Fairy}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=VII}}\n{{Dex/Gen/3|gen=VII|reg1=Alola|num1=174|label1={{gameabbrev7|SM}}:|reg2=Alola|num2=210|label2={{gameabbrev7|USUM}}:|reg3=Kanto}}\n{{Dex/NE|[[Pokémon: Let\'s Go, Pikachu! and Let\'s Go, Eevee!|Let\'s Go, Pikachu! and Let\'s Go, Eevee!]]\u200e}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Sun|entry=It attaches flowers to its highly nutritious vine. This revitalizes the flowers, and they give off an aromatic scent.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Moon|entry=Baths prepared with the flowers from its vine have a relaxing effect, so this Pokémon is a hit with many people.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Ultra Sun|entry=It stretches sticky vines out from its head and picks flowers to adorn itself with. When it doesn\'t have any flowers, it feels uneasy.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Ultra Moon|entry=It picks flowers and sticks them to its body with fluids it produces. The aroma that wafts from its petals has a healing effect.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Footer}}\n\n===Game locations===\n{{Availability/Header|type=Fairy}}\n{{Availability/NA|gen=VII}}\n{{Availability/Gen|gen=VII}}\n{{Availability/Entry2|v=Sun|v2=Moon|area=[[Lush Jungle]]}}\n{{Availability/Entry2|v=Ultra Sun|v2=Ultra Moon|area=[[Lush Jungle]], [[Poké Pelago]]{{tt|*|Only begin appearing after the player reaches Ula\'Ula Island}}}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Availability/Footer}}\n\n====In side games====\n{{Availability/Header|type=Fairy}}\n{{Availability/Cross}}\n{{Availability/Entry1|1|v=Shuffle|color={{beauty color}}|area=Event: \'\'[[Special Stages#Great Challenge|Comfey Appears]]\'\'}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Availability/Footer}}\n\n====In events====\n{{eventAvail/h|Region|type=Fairy}}\n{{eventAvail|{{gameabbrev7|SM}}|Pokémon Center Birthday Comfey|All|Japan|10|November 18, 2016 to ???|link=List of local event Pokémon distributions in Generation VII#Comfey}}\n|}\n\n===Held items===\n{{HeldItems\n|type=Fairy\n|sm1=Misty Seed|sm1type=None|sm1rar=5\n|usum1=Misty Seed|usum1type=None|usum1rar=5\n}}\n\n===Stats===\n====Base stats====\n{{Stats\n|type=Fairy\n|HP=51\n|Attack=52\n|Defense=90\n|SpAtk=82\n|SpDef=110\n|Speed=100}}\n\n===Type effectiveness===\n{{TypeEffectiveness\n|type1=Fairy\n|Normal=100\n|Fighting=50\n|Flying=100\n|Poison=200\n|Ground=100\n|Rock=100\n|Bug=50\n|Ghost=100\n|Steel=200\n|Fire=100\n|Water=100\n|Grass=100\n|Electric=100\n|Psychic=100\n|Ice=100\n|Dragon=0\n|Dark=50\n|Fairy=